From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 10:57:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] make: route kati diagnostics to the builtin's fds; don't exit
 the process
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two correctness bugs for the in-process make builtin, both around recipe
failure / diagnostics:

1. RECIPE FAILURE KILLED THE ENGINE. kati's exec called std::process::exit(2)
   on a failing recipe — fine for the shadow process, fatal for a builtin
   (it killed the whole brush/engine process). Now exec emits the
   `*** [target] Error N` line and returns a BuildFailed(code) error that
   unwinds to make_main/make_builtin (which return the code) and to the
   standalone rkati main (which downcasts it to its exit). No re-print.

2. DIAGNOSTICS ESCAPED THE BRUSH PIPE. Recipe stdout was already routed to the
   builtin's context fd 1; recipe-failure lines, $(warning)/warn!/kati_warn,
   and $(info) still went to the PROCESS stdout/stderr, so a nested make's
   messages bypassed the parent's pipe. Added a RECIPE_ERR thread-local sink
   beside RECIPE_OUT; routed exec's error lines, lib.rs's color_warn_log +
   warn!/kati_warn macros, and func's $(info) through them. make_builtin sets
   both fd 1 and fd 2 from its ExecutionContext (save/restore for nesting).
   (Parse/eval $(error)s already propagated as anyhow and were routed.)

Validated: test_make_rs CASE 9 — a failing recipe in a recursive sub-make exits
the box cleanly (code 2), routes BOTH `*** [boom] Error 1` (sub-make) and
`*** [all] Error 2` (parent) up the pipe, and the engine survives (no make
rows, no process death). Standalone unchanged: kati corpus 364/378 fail=0
(same recipe-failure output + exit 2); full box suite MAKE-RS PASS.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
